During the course an overview is given of the Stone Age archaeological historiography and the most influential researchers in Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania. In addition Stone Age archaeological cultures as well as the most important sites and single finds from the Baltic countries are introduced.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to present a detailed overview of Estonian, Latvian and Lithuanian Stone Age (the historiography, sites, finds).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course: * can name the most important researchers of the Stone Age in the Baltic countries and knows the main trends of the Stone Age historiography; * knows the main archaeological cultures in the Baltic countries during the Stone Age; * can name the most important Stone Age sites in the Baltic countries; * can find similarities and differences between the Stone Age archaeological material of Estonia Latvia and Lithuania; * can describe the most important cultural and economic processes and analyze the development of the society during the Stone Age in the Baltic countries; * knows how to find additional information (publications, databases, etc., facilities) on the matter.
